==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Gymnasium
<hw>Gym*na"si*um</hw> <pr>(j⟦icr⟧m*n⟦amac⟧"z⟦icr⟧*⟦ucr⟧m <it>or</it>
j⟦icr⟧m*n⟦amac⟧"zh⟦icr⟧*⟦ucr⟧m; 277)</pr> <pos>n.</pos>;
<plu><it>pl.</it> E. <plw>Gymnasiums</plw>
<pr>(j⟦icr⟧m*n⟦amac⟧"z⟦icr⟧*⟦ucr⟧mz)</pr>, L. <plw>Gymnasia</plw>
<pr>(j⟦icr⟧m*n⟦amac⟧"z⟦icr⟧*⟦adot⟧)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[L., fr. Gr.
<grk>gymna`sion</grk>, fr. <grk>gymna`zein</grk> to exercise (naked),
fr. <grk>gymo`s</grk> naked.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A place or building
where athletic exercises are performed; a school for
gymnastics.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A school for the higher branches of literature and
science; a preparatory school for the university; -- used esp. of German
schools of this kind.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>More like ordinary schools of <qex>gymnasia</qex> than
universities.</q> <rj><qau>Hallam.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Gymnast</ent>⟦br⟧
